title: PPPP’s Mir Nadir Ali Magsi wins PS-14 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Pakistan People’s Party Parliamentarians’ (PPPP), Mi Nadir Ali Magsi has won the Sindh Assembly election from PS-14, Qambar Shahdadokot by securing 38,473 votes.
According to unofficial result issued by Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Muzaffar Ali Brohi of Grand Democratic Alliance, who bagged votes 20,422.
Overall voters’ turn-out remained 33.58 %.
